SIMPLE: imminent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imminent
<hw>Im"mi*nent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imminens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>imminere</ets> to project; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>minere</ets> (in comp.) to jut, project. See
<er>Eminent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Threatening to occur
immediately; near at hand; impending; -- said especially of misfortune
or peril.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In danger <xex>imminent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of danger; threatening; menacing;
perilous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hairbreadth scapes i' the <qex>imminent</qex> deadly breach.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>(With <xex>upon</xex>) Bent upon; attentive
to.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their eyes ever <qex>imminent</qex> upon worldly matters.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impending; threatening; near; at hand.</syn> --
<usage><er>Imminent</er>, <er>Impending</er>, <er>Threatening</er>.
<xex>Imminent</xex> is the strongest: it denotes that something is ready
to fall or happen on the instant; as, in <xex>imminent</xex> danger of
one's life. <xex>Impending</xex> denotes that something hangs suspended
over us, and may so remain indefinitely; as, the <xex>impending</xex>
evils of war. <xex>Threatening</xex> supposes some danger in prospect,
but more remote; as, <xex>threatening</xex> indications for the
future.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Three times to-day⟦br⟧
You have defended me from <qex>imminent</qex> death.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No story I unfold of public woes,⟦br⟧
Nor bear advices of <qex>impending</qex> foes.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fierce faces <qex>threatening</qex> war.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imminently</ent>⟦br⟧
